 Cash]] <small>(2016\u2013)</small>\n| theme_music_composer = [[Kodaline]] \u2013 \"Perfect World\" & \"Brand New Day\"\n| country            = [[United Kingdom]]\n| language           = English\n| num_series         = 15\n| num_episodes       = 193 <!-- As of 3 April 2020 -->\n| list_episodes      = List of Gogglebox episodes\n| executive_producer = Tania Alexander<ref name=\"Telegraph\">\n{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/10480336/Gogglebox-the-TV-show-making-Britain-feel-great.html|title=Gogglebox: the TV show making Britain feel great|last=McNulty|first=Bernadette|date=18 December 2013|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|accessdate=19 December 2013}}</ref>\n| camera             = [[Multiple-camera setup|Dual cameras]]\n| runtime            = 50 minutes <small>(series 1\u20132)</small><br>60 minutes <small>(series 3\u2013)</small>\n| company            = [[Studio Lambert]]<ref name=\"Standard\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/london-life/watching-you-watching-me-why-c4-show-gogglebox-is-set-to-go-global-9012355.html|title=Watching you, watching me: why C4 show Gogglebox is set to go global|last=Spanier|first=Gideon|date=18 December 2013|work=[[London Evening Standard]]|accessdate=19 December 2013}}</ref>\n| distributor        = [[All3Media]]<ref name=\"Standard\"/>\n| picture_format     = [[16:9]]\n| audio_format       = Stereo\n| first_aired        = {{Start date|df=y|2013|3|7}}\n| last_aired         = present\n| website            = http://www.channel4.com/programmes/gogglebox/\n| production_website = http://www.studiolambert.com/gogglebox.html\n| channel            = [[Channel 4]]\n}}\n'''''Gogglebox''''' is a [[British television]] reality series that premiered on [[Channel 4]] on 7 March 2013. The programme features a number of families and groups of friends from different places around the United Kingdom who [[Reaction video|react to]] British television programmes from their own homes. The series won a [[British Academy Television Awards|BAFTA]] award in 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/baftas/10839903/Baftas-view-from-the-other-side-of-the-screen.html|title=BAFTA's view from the other side of the screen|date=18 May 2014|work=Telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> and a [[National Television Award]] in 2015, 2016, 2017, and 2018.\n\nA version of the series featuring children, titled ''Gogglesprogs'', launched as a Christmas special on Christmas Day 2015, and was followed by a full-length series which began airing on 17 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/info/press/news/c4-follow-up-xmas-gogglebox-kids-special-with-series-order|title=C4 follow up Xmas Gogglebox Kids special with series order|date=14 December 2015|work=[[Channel 4]]|accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref> In 2017, a spin-off series titled ''Vlogglebox'' aired on [[E4 (TV channel)|E4]], which featured reactions from 16 to 24-year-olds as they watch online content on their smartphones, laptops or tablets.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/gogglebox/news/a829505/gogglebox-getting-teenager-spinoff-called-vlogglebox/|title=Gogglebox gets a teenager spin-off called Vlogglebox|last=Houghton|first=Rianne|date=30 May 2017|work=[[Digital Spy]]}}</ref> Shortly after the thirteenth series of ''Gogglebox'' finished, it was announced that a celebrity version had been ordered; ''[[List of Gogglebox episodes#Celebrity Gogglebox|Celebrity Gogglebox]]'' began airing on 14 June 2019.\n\n''Gogglebox'' was narrated from its launch on 7 March 2013 until 1 April 2016 by [[Caroline Aherne]]. She was diagnosed with [[lung cancer]] in 2014, which led to her death on 2 July 2016. [[Craig Cash]] regularly filled in for Aherne when she was unavailable and took over the role as narrator permanently on 8 April 2016.\n\n==Production==\nThe programme is a production of [[Studio Lambert]], a company run by British [[media executive]] [[Stephen Lambert (media executive)|Stephen Lambert]], who was behind other [[Channel 4]] programmes such as ''[[Faking It (UK TV series)|Faking It]]'', ''[[Wife Swap (UK TV series)|Wife Swap]]'', ''[[Undercover Boss]]'' and ''[[The Secret Millionaire]]''.\n\nDirector of Factual Entertainment for Studio Lambert Tania Alexander, the executive producer and person responsible for the TV series, said the original idea was for the programme to be a \"mix of ''[[Harry Hill's TV Burp|Harry Hill]]'' and ''[[The Royle Family]]''\" but with real people.<ref name=\"Telegraph\" />\n\nThe Creative Director for Studio Lambert Tim Harcourt had the original idea for the programme while watching the [[London riots 2011|London riots]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/gogglebox-axe-celebrity-big-brother-4092564|title=Gogglebox axe for Celebrity Big Brother star George Gilbey and family|last=Methven|first=Nicola|date=22 August 2014|work=Daily Mirror|access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.studiolambert.com/tim-harcourt.html|title=Tim Harcourt|last=Arrow|first=Platinum|website=www.studiolambert.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-26}}</ref> and along with Alexander devised the format for the show. They wondered what people were talking about while watching the news and came up with the idea of cutting between people watching the same TV programmes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/gogglebox-axe-celebrity-big-brother-4092564|title=George Gilbey's family AXED from Gogglebox due to CBB appearance|last=Methven|first=Nicola|date=2014-08-22|work=Daily Mirror|access-date=2017-10-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/03/20/watching-us-watching-them-on-the-people-s-couch|title=Watching Us, Watching Them: On \u2018The People\u2019s Couch\u2019|last=Teeman|first=Tim|date=2014-03-20|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=2017-10-26}}</ref>\n\nFarah Ramzan Golant, the boss of [[All3Media]], said: \"Everyone loves watching TV and talking about TV. But the show isn't really about TV. The show is about people's lives, their relationships, their living rooms and the way children and parents talk about TV. It's near real-time because you're watching what happened in the seven days before. That's quite priceless. It captures a cultural response to something that's happening in the world. Gogglebox shows TV in people's living rooms is alive and well and thriving. It is asserting the indispensable role of TV in the fabric of people's lives.\"<ref name=\"Standard\"/>\n\n===Filming===\nThe programme is filmed in the viewers' homes, by two small HD remote-control cameras<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shooting-partners.co.uk/gogglebox-2/ |title=Gogglebox 2 |publisher=Shooting Partners |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> known as \"hot heads\", operated by a small team elsewhere in the home that have set up a temporary [[production control room]]; the team consists of a producer/director, gallery operator, assistant, audio engineer, researcher (for live logging) and a [[Television crew#Runner|runner]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/academy/production/article/art20131104163905281 |title=I made... Gogglebox |last=Cahn |first=John |publisher=BBC |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{{main|List of Gogglebox cast members}}\nThis is a list of cast members currently appearing in the programme.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:400px;\"|Cast members\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|Series\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Year\n|-\n| Stephen Webb\n| 1\u2013\n| 2013\u2013\n|-\n| Siddiqui family (Sid, Umar and Baasit)\n| 1\u2013\n| 2013\u2013\n|-\n| Michael family (Andrew, Carolyne, Louis, Alex and Katie)\n| 1\u20134, 6\u2013\n| 2013\u2013\n|-\n| Linda and Peter McGarry, and [[George Gilbey]]\n| 2\u20133, 7\u2013\n| 2013\u20132014, 2016\u2013\n|-\n| Woerdenweber family (Ralf, Viv and Evie)\n| 2\u2013\n| 2013\u2013\n|-\n| [[William Hartston]] and Josef Kollar\n| 2\u2013\n| 2013\u2013\n|-\n| Malone family (Tom, Julie, Tom Jnr and Shaun)\n| 4\u2013\n| 2014\u2013\n|-\n| Jenny and Lee\n| 4\u2013\n| 2014\u2013\n|-\n| Giles Wood and [[Mary Killen]]\n| 5\u2013\n| 2015\u2013\n|-\n| Ellie and Izzi Warner\n| 6\u2013\n| 2015\u2013\n|-\n| Dave and Shirley\n| 6\u2013\n| 2015\u2013\n|-\n| McCormick family (Scott, Georgia and Isaac)\n| 7\u2013\n| 2016\u2013\n|-\n| Plummer family (Tremaine, Twaine and Tristan)\n| 7\u2013\n| 2016\u2013\n|-\n| Mary and Marina\n| 8\u2013\n| 2016\u2013\n|-\n| Amira, Amani and Iqra\n| 10\u2013\n| 2017\u2013\n|-\n| Alison, George and Helena\n| 10\u2013\n| 2017\u2013\n|-\n| Pete and Sophie Sandiford\n| 10\u2013\n| 2017\u2013\n|-\n| Marcus, Mica, Sachelle and Shuggy\n| 11\u2013\n| 2018\u2013\n|-\n| John and Beryl\n| 12\u2013\n| 2018\u2013\n|-\n| Abbie and Georgia\n| 12\u2013\n| 2018\u2013\n|-\n| Daniel Lustig\n| 13\u2013\n| 2019\u2013\n|-\n| Anne and Ken\n| 15\u2013\n| 2020\u2013\n|}\n\n===Other appearances===\nAs well as appearing on ''Gogglebox'', some of the cast members have competed in other reality series, including ''[[Celebrity Big Brother (UK TV series)|Celebrity Big Brother]]'', ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK TV series)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]'', and ''[[The Jump]]''.\n\n*''[[Celebrity Big Brother (UK TV series)|Celebrity Big Brother]]''\n**[[George Gilbey]] \u2013 [[Celebrity Big Brother 14|Series 14]] (2014) \u2013 Fourth<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/celebrity-big-brother-final-george-4235033|title=Celebrity Big Brother final: George Gilbey evicted after SNOGGING Edele Lynch|first=Carl|last=Greenwood|date=12 September 2014|publisher=}}</ref>\n**[[Sandi Bogle]] \u2013 [[Celebrity Big Brother 20|Series 20]] (2017) \u2013 Ninth\n*''[[The Jump]]''\n**[[Dominic Parker]] \u2013 [[The Jump (series 2)|Series 2]] (2015) \u2013 Fifteenth<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/gogglebox-star-dom-parker-injured-5052944|title=Gogglebox star Dom Parker INJURED in crash on The Jump|first=Danny|last=Walker|date=27 January 2015|work=Daily Mirror}}</ref>\n*''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK TV series)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]''\n**[[Scarlett Moffatt]] \u2013 [[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK series 16)|Series 16]] (2016) \u2013 Winner<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3914486/ |title='There's life in the old bird yet': Carol Vorderman leads the new jungle pack alongside Lisa Snowdon and Scarlett Moffatt as full 2016 I'm A Celebrity line-up is revealed |date=7 November 2016 |first=JJ |last=Nattrass |publisher=[[MailOnline]] |accessdate=8 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/im-a-celebrity/news/a815982/im-a-celebrity-scarlett-is-crowned-the-queen-of-the-jungle/|title=I'm a Celeb: Scarlett is crowned Queen of the Jungle|date=4 December 2016|work=Daily Mirror}}</ref>\n*''[[Celebs on the Farm]]''\n**Sandi Bogle \u2013 Series 1 (2018) \u2013 Seventh\n\n==Transmissions==\n{{main|List of Gogglebox episodes}}\n{{:List of Gogglebox episodes}}\n\n===''Celebrity Gogglebox''===\nFrom 14 June 2019 to 19 July, a celebrity version of the series was broadcast, titled ''[[List of Gogglebox episodes#Celebrity Gogglebox|Celebrity Gogglebox]]''. Stars featured on the series included [[Little Mix]], [[Jessie J]], [[Olly Alexander]], [[Rylan Clark-Neal]], [[Sunetra Sarker]], [[Georgia Toffolo]] and others.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Award !! Year !! Result\n|-\n| '''[[British Academy Television Awards|BAFTA TV Award]]''' for \"Reality & Constructed Factual Programme\" || 2014 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[British Academy Television Awards|BAFTA TV Award]]''' for \"Radio Times Audience Award\" || 2014 || {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''[[Broadcasting Press Guild]]''' for \"Best Factual Entertainment Programme\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadcastingpressguild.org/bpgawards/2014-winners/|title=2014|work=Broadcasting Press Guild}}</ref> || 2014 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[National Television Awards|National Television Award]]''' for \"Factual Programme\" || 2015 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[TV Choice Award]]''' for \"Factual Entertainment Show\" || 2015 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[National Television Awards|National Television Award]]''' for \"Factual Programme\" ||  2016 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[British Academy Television Awards|BAFTA TV Award]]''' for \"Reality & Constructed Factual Programme\" || 2016 || {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''[[TV Choice Award]]''' for \"Lifestyle Show\" || 2016 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[BBC Radio 1|Radio 1's Teen Award]]''' for \"TV Show\" || 2016 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[National Television Awards|National Television Award]]''' for \"Factual Entertainment\" ||  2017 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''Diversity in Media Awards''' for \"TV Programme of the Year\" ||  2017 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[National Television Awards|National Television Award]]''' for \"Factual Entertainment\" ||  2018 || {{won}}\n|-\n| '''[[National Television Awards|National Television Award]]''' for \"Factual Entertainment\" || 2019 || {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''[[National Television Awards|National Television Award]]''' for \"Factual Entertainment\" || 2020 || {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==International versions==\n\n===Australian version===\n{{main|Gogglebox Australia}}\nAn Australian edition of the programme debuted on 11 February 2015. It is a co-production between pay TV provider [[Foxtel]] and commercial [[Network Ten]]. It airs on Foxtel's [[Lifestyle (Australian TV channel)|Lifestyle Channel]] first and is repeated 24 hours later on Ten.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/10/gogglebox-to-premiere-on-foxtel-one-night-ten-the-next.html|title=Gogglebox to premiere on Foxtel one night, TEN the next.|work=tvtonight.com.au}}</ref> The programme started its second season on 30 September 2015,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Gogglebox Australia: season 2 will get you talking|url = https://www.foxtel.com.au/got/whats-on/foxtel-insider/lifestyle/gogglebox-australia.html|website = www.foxtel.com.au|accessdate = 2015-10-15}}</ref> and its third season in 2016. It had shown 8 episodes of the 4th season as of December 2016.\n\n===United States/Canadian version===\n{{main|The People's Couch}}\nCanadian ([[Bell Media]]),<ref>{{cite web|title=Gogglebox Canada casting call|url=http://goggleboxca.com}}</ref> and American broadcasters. The American and Canadian versions, both called ''[[The People's Couch]]'', premiered on [[Bravo (U.S. TV network)|Bravo]] on 10 March 2014 (although a three-episode pilot run was aired in October 2013) and [[Bravo (Canada)]] in July 2014.<ref name=\"Standard\"/><ref name=\"Guardian\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2013/dec/17/channel-4-gogglebox-goes-global|title=Channel 4 hit show Gogglebox goes global|last=Plunkett|first=John|date=17 December 2013|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=19 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bellmediapr.ca/Network/Bravo/Press/Everyones-a-Critic-All-New-Canadian-Unscripted-Series-THE-PEOPLES-COUCH-Gets-Cozy-on-Bravo-July-13|title=Everyone's a Critic. All-New Canadian Unscripted Series, THE PEOPLE's COUCH Gets Cozy on Bravo July 13 |accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===''Gogglebox'' around the world===\n:{{Color box|#90EE90|border=darkgray}} Currently airing\n:{{Color box|#FFC0CB|border=darkgray}} No longer airing\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:100%; line-height:15px;\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! Country\n! Name\n! Channel\n! Date aired\n! Series\n|-\n| style=\"background:#90EE90;\" align=\"left\" |'''{{flag|Australia}}'''\n| ''[[Gogglebox Australia]]''\n| [[Lifestyle (Australian TV channel)|Lifestyle]] and [[Network Ten]]\n| 11 February 2015 \u2013 present\n| \nSeries 1, 2015<br />\nSeries 2, 2015<br />\nSeries 3, 2016<br />\nSeries 4, 2016<br />\nSeries 5, 2017<br />\nSeries 6, 2017<br />\nSeries 7, 2018<br />\nSeries 8, 2018<br />\n|-\n| style=\"background:#90EE90;\" align=\"left\" rowspan=2